# Aceso environment template.
#
# Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in the values you actually use.
# Source of truth for the variable list is agent/config.go:loadConfig.
# Anything not set here falls back to the default shown next to it.
#
# Architectural note: Aceso is local-only by design. The binary contains
# no code paths to third-party LLM APIs (DeepSeek, Gemini, OpenAI, etc.)
# and never will — see CLAUDE.md "Inference is local-only". If the local
# Ollama instance is unreachable, alerts are escalated to a human via
# the structured log line and (optionally) ntfy.sh; the agent does not
# silently route around the outage.

# --- Required ---------------------------------------------------------------

# Base URLs for the three observe-loop dependencies. No trailing slash.
# In production the monitoring stack lives on an external Docker network
# named "monitoring"; in dev (docker-compose.dev.yml) these resolve via
# the bridge network.
PROMETHEUS_URL=http://prometheus:9090
LOKI_URL=http://loki:3100

# Ollama is the only LLM backend. In production the recommended topology
# is a 16 GB Raspberry Pi running Ollama, reached over a plain WireGuard
# tunnel from the VPS — point this at the Pi's WireGuard IP, e.g.
# http://10.10.0.2:11434 (see docs/adr/003-plain-wireguard-over-tailscale.md
# and docs/pi-deploy.md). In dev, point at a local Ollama container.
OLLAMA_URL=http://ollama:11434

# --- LLM chain (optional) ---------------------------------------------------

# Order in which backends are tried. V0 only supports "ollama"; the field
# exists so future revisions can chain a second local path (e.g. an
# on-VPS small model) without restructuring the code. Unknown names are
# logged and skipped at startup; if no usable backend remains, aceso
# refuses to start (running with no inference path is a misconfiguration,
# not a degraded mode).
BACKEND_ORDER=ollama

# --- Escalation (optional) --------------------------------------------------

# When every backend in the chain fails, aceso escalates the alert to a
# human instead of inventing a diagnosis. The structured log line is
# always emitted (free, goes into whatever shipper is already capturing
# stdout). Set ESCALATE_NTFY_URL to additionally send an ntfy.sh push.
#
# Pick an unguessable topic suffix — ntfy topics are public.
# Example: https://ntfy.sh/aceso-emil-7f3a9b
# For a self-hosted deployment, point this at your own ntfy server.
ESCALATE_NTFY_URL=

# --- Tunables (optional) ----------------------------------------------------

# Any locally-pulled Ollama model. gemma2:2b fits a 4 GB VPS; on a 16 GB
# Pi you can comfortably run larger models (e.g. qwen2.5:7b at Q4).
OLLAMA_MODEL=gemma2:2b

# Cadence of the observe loop, in seconds.
POLL_INTERVAL_SECONDS=30

# Per-call timeout (Prometheus, Loki, Ollama, ntfy). Ollama's first
# generation after a cold load can be slow — keep this generous.
HTTP_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=120

# Where the NDJSON incident log lives. /data is a named Docker volume in
# both compose files; use a host path for non-Docker dev runs.
INCIDENTS_PATH=/data/incidents.json
